This paper proposes an improved training algorithm for Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN) to address mode collapse and gradient vanishing issues. The proposed method involves using an Autoencoder (AE) to constrain the generator and introducing two novel distance constraints to improve the generator. The paper presents results on benchmark datasets such as MNIST, CelebA, CIFAR-10, and STL-10. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound).
